# Security hardening

## Beta 0 identity boundary (invite-only)

Persisted portfolios/strategies for Beta accounts use **Supabase Auth + Postgres
RLS** (`supabase/schema.sql`). Sign-up requires a **one-time invite code**.
Admin Captain (`profiles.role = admin`) vs beta. Local and Cloudflare share the
same Supabase project when env vars match.

- SPA: `VITE_SUPABASE_URL`, `VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`
- Worker: `SUPABASE_URL`, `SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` (JWT check on `/api/market/*` when
  configured; set `MARKET_AUTH_REQUIRED=false` for open local market proxy)
- Demo Captain (`ENABLE_DEMO_GATE=true`) is **legacy only** — not a save path
  for personal holdings

## STOP and remind before

- Real brokerage/account connections (Webull, E*Trade, MooMoo, Plaid, OAuth)
- Putting **unauthenticated** or shared-demo password saves in front of real
  personal/financial data
- Shipping secrets in the SPA bundle

## What to say if someone proposes Demo-persisted real books

> "Demo Captain is retired for saved Beta work. Personal strategies/holdings go
> behind invite-only Supabase accounts with RLS. Want to issue an invite and use
> Admin Captain instead?"

Do not silently put real-data persistence back on the B1 demo cookie.
